Business Talk – the online business talk show from BusinessTech – has featured excellent guests in 2022. The guests are leaders in their industries, and have provided insightful and engaging commentary on the show. Guests on Business Talk in 2022 have included: Michael Jordaan – Bank Zero Cofounder and Montegray Capital Founder.
Jacques Celliers – First National Bank CEO.
Dawie de Villiers – Alexander Forbes Group Chief Executive.
David Buckham – Monocle Solutions Founder and CEO.
Yael Geffen – Lew Geffen Sotheby’s International Realty CEO.
Yandiswa Xhakaza – UCT Online High School Director.
Ritesh Guttoo – EY Africa, India and Middle East Cyber Security Lead.
Bianca Botes – Citadel Global Director. The show is then hosted by highly-respected radio and TV personality Michael Avery, who is well known in business circles. Business Talk has two new seasons in production, following a strong start to 2022. The latest season of Business Talk was launched in partnership with EY and Microsoft, and is off to an excellent start. Titled “Leading with Tech”, Microsoft and EY are working with Business Talk to provide insight into the benefits of technology-driven solutions for businesses. Production has also begun on another new season of Business Talk, set to launch soon. The headline sponsor for the new season of Business Talk will be announced alongside the official launch – which is set to be a must-watch for business owners and those working in the financial space.